'''Benjamin S. Hale''' is an [[Environmental philosophy|environmental philosopher]] and [[Environmental ethics|ethicist]]. He is currently Associate Professor of Philosophy and Environmental Studies at the [[University of Colorado Boulder|University of Colorado–Boulder]], as well as a faculty affiliate at the university's Center for Science and Technology Policy Research<ref>https://www.colorado.edu/philosophy/benjamin-hale</ref>.
Hale is President of the [[International Society for Environmental Ethics]]<ref>https://enviroethics.org/officers/</ref> and co-editor of the journal ''Ethics, Policy & Environment''<ref>https://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=editorialBoard&journalCode=cepe21</ref>.
