'''Viswamaanava''' is a [[Hindu]] cultural [[ideology]]. ''Viswa'' means [[Universality (philosophy)|universal]] and ''maanava'' means [[human]].  This ideology is inherent in all Indian [[scripture]]s, [[culture]], and [[tradition]]s. It is extensively discussed and partially practised in [[Advaita Vedanta]] traditions.  Many great intellectuals lived by this principle and contributed to the welfare of the underprivileged sections of society.

